column2: Algae.  Also lots of rain.  Some resorts have strong sewer/septic smells.  Surface temp 70 F.
In the last week (9/5 through 9/12)- we've had over 8" of rain + 60-65 F daytime highs.
Algae bloom- 40 F air temp.  Surf temp 58 F.
Oct 7 had less algae than October 2.  Water less green on October 7 than October 2.
Mostly clear of algae.  Tons + tons of leaves in the water the past week.  Mostly oak + birch.  Surface temp 46 F.
35 F ambient air temp- pH approximately 4.5- surface temp 43 F.
Sunny- W wind 10 mph- night temps in mid 30s to lower 40s- day temps upper 50s to low 60s- about 2.5" rain last 12 days- algal apparent at sample site- brown algae in northern end of lake
Weeks of stormy weather.  No sun.  Surf temp 62 F.
A very cool wet spring-summer so far.  Surface temp 64 f
Rained from 9 in the evening to 10 am today.  Surf temp 65 F.
Surf temp 70 F.  Some algae coming slight green color.
Green (algae ) clumps (1/4" diameter) floating on surface.  Surface temp 65 F.
Mostly sunny- the surface temperature is 62 degrees F- and there are some algal blooms.
Surface temp 58 F.  Ambient temp Thursday am was 38 f
Beautiful warm days prior to reading.  Surface temp 58 f
Approx. 2.5 rain in the past 7 days some algae blooms near the surface.  Assumed noon for sample time.
Cool weather has turned most of lake over.
Dark.  Assumed sample time was noon.
Secchi depth was taken from lab sheet- no data sheet sent for this date.
Surface temp. 56 degrees.  Bright sunny day just after 2 days rain.
Surface temp. 64 degrees.  Bright - sunny calm day.
Surface temp. 69 degrees F.  One week of hot humid weather.
Surface temp. 80 degrees.  Over a week plus of 90 degrees weather and no rain.
Several days of cold wet weather- surface temp. 70 degrees f
A little rain + cool for 2 days- surface temp. 67 degrees
Surface temp. 74 degrees- rained hard evening of 7/19/95.
Surface temp. 74 degrees.  After 4.5" rain the 6th and 7th.
Previous 8 days has produced 6.5" of rain- weather is hot and humid in the past 30 days.
Two days of rain- last two days sun- surface lake temp. 72 degrees f
Nice sunny day- very calm- floating green algae.  Previous week very cold and 40 degrees.
Nice warm 85 degrees F for three days.
Surface temp. 70 degrees F. small rains last night.
Surface temp. 74 degrees. rain brought junk in from mud lake into site e.
Temp. 53 degrees F (water) . beautiful fall day. been rain free for 1 week.
sunni. clear day- heavy rain last night
cloudy- breezy. Rained 3/4 inch last night
